{"batchcomplete": "", "query": {"pages": {"1858215": {"pageid": 1858215, "ns": 0, "title": "Eternal Flame (song)", "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "pagelanguagehtmlcode": "en", "pagelanguagedir": "ltr", "touched": "2026-02-19T12:15:12Z", "lastrevid": 1338734268, "length": 56060, "fullurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eternal_Flame_(song)", "editurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Eternal_Flame_(song)&action=edit", "canonicalurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eternal_Flame_(song)", "pageprops": {"defaultsort": "Eternal Flame (Song)", "page_image": "Eternal_Flame_by_The_Bangles_US_commercial_cassette.png", "wikibase-shortdesc": "1989 song by the Bangles", "wikibase_item": "Q1371048"}, "description": "1989 song by the Bangles", "descriptionsource": "local", "extract": "\"Eternal Flame\" is a song by American pop rock group the Bangles for their third studio album, Everything (1988). Released on January 23, 1989 by CBS, the power ballad was written by group member Susanna Hoffs with the established hit songwriting team of Billy Steinberg and Tom Kelly. Davitt Sigerson produced it. \nUpon its 1989 single release, \"Eternal Flame\" became a number-one hit in nine countries, including Australia, Sweden, the United Kingdom, and the United States. Since its release, it has been covered by many musical artists, including Australian boy band Human Nature, who reached the Australian top 10 with their version, and British girl group Atomic Kitten, who topped four national charts with their rendition.", "categories": [{"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1980s ballads"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1988 songs"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1989 singles"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1997 singles"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1999 singles"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2001 singles"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:3T songs"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All articles with dead external links"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All articles wi